column2: 발트해의 슈체친에서 아드리아헤의 트리에스테까지, 유럽을 가로질러 철의 장막이 내려왔습니다. 이 장막 뒤에는 중앙/동유럽의 모든 오랜 국가들이 자리잡고 있습니다. 그림자는 최근 연합군이 승리하면서 드리워졌습니다. 소련과 그의 공산주의 국제기구가 가까운 미래에 무엇을 하려고 하는지, 그들의 확장적인 성향에 한계가 있는지 아무도 모릅니다. 세계의 안전은 어느 국가도 소외되지 않는 유럽의 새로운 단결을 필요로 합니다. 20세기, 특히 전후에 유럽이 국민국가를 독립시키는 일이 전 세계적으로 일어났습니다. 수세기 동안 타문화의 권력에 의존하며 살아온 사람들에게서 민족 의식이 각성했습니다. 여러 인종과 문명을 가진 많은 나라들은 독립적인 소수 문화를 압박했습니다. 구세계 강대국들이 좋아하든 싫어하든 변화의 바람이 옛 식민지에 불고 있는데, 이런 민족 의식의 성장은 정치적 사실입니다. 새로운 전쟁이 지난 전쟁의 잿더미를 깨고 동/서유럽을 강타하는 혼란 사이에서 일어나고 있습니다. 냉전입니다.
column3: From Stettin in the Baltic to Trieste in the Adriatic, an iron curtain has descended across the Continent. Behind that line lie all the capitals of the ancient states of Central, and Eastern Europe. A shadow has fallen upon the scenes so lately lighted by the Allied victory. Nobody knows what Soviet Russia and its Communist international organisation intends to do in the immediate future, or what are the limits, if any, to their expansive and proselytising tendencies. The safety of the world requires a new unity in Europe, from which no nation should be permanently outcast. In the twentieth century, and especially since the end of the war, the processes which gave birth to the nation states of Europe have been repeated all over the world. There have been the awakening of national consciousness in peoples who have for centuries lived in dependence upon some other power. Many countries of different races and civilisations, pressed their claim to an independent national life. The wind of change is blowing through the colonised world, and whether the old world powers like it or not, this growth of national consciousness is a political fact. From the ashes of the last war, a new war is brewing amongst the turmoil, one that pits East vs West. This is the Cold War.

column3: Gorbachev tear down this wall! Few would have thought that the Iron Curtain would have fallen so quickly but yet it did. This sparked a chain reaction which quickly reverberated throughout the world. The USSR rapidly decended into a pulpit of pandemonium that would culminate into its dissolution. America is now the world hegemon. However it will not last long in this new multi-polar world with the rise of new centers of power in the ambitious and populace east. China and India are aspiring to seize the top spot to end the American hegemony though soft and hard power. With globalisation and the shift in geopolitical power towards the east, this is increasingly not a matter of if but when. In this renewed competitive multipolar world, nations will join what are initially trade blocs, and eventually in some cases large centralised union states like the European Union, the South American Union and the African Union. All the while new conflicts ignite over the shattered remains of the eastern bloc. In light of these developments, the end of the Cold War can hardly have said to deliver the decisive realisation of international peace but it still has profundly altered our world and whether it is for the better or worse is up to you. This is the beginning of the New World Order.

column2: Schwerpunkt(종심)는 '결정적인 조치가 이루어질 수 있는 중력의 중심 또는 최대 노력의 지점'을 가리키는 용어입니다. 따라서 지상의 기계화 부대와 공군력은 가능하다면 항상 최대한의 노력을 기울이는 시점에 집중적으로 투입됩니다. 이후에는 적의 후방에서 전투를 벌여 소규모의 병력이 돌파구를 마련해 이점을 얻습니다. 구데리안은 이 교리를 'Klotzen, nicht kleckern!'으로 요약했는데, 이는 '추상적으로 말고, 힘 있게 행동하라'는 의미입니다.
column3: Schwerpunkt is a term reffering to the 'center of gravity or point of maximum effort, where a decisive action could be achieved'. Ground, mechanised and tactical air forces could be concentrated at this point of maximum effort whenever possible. By local success at the Schwerpunkt, a small force achieved a breakthrough and gained advantages by fighting in the enemy's rear. Guderian summarized this doctrine as 'Klotzen, nicht kleckern!' meaning 'act powerfully, not superficially'.
